"Picked up a four pack of this one this afternoon (kind of on a black ale kick for some reason). Poured a nice, rich dark brown color, with some reddish highlights and a big light brown head. Aromas of dark chocolate, earthy hops and light coffee. On the palate, this one is medium bodied, with flavors of milk and dark chocolate, vanilla and earthy hops, with a lingering bitter finish."
